The paper deals with optimization problems related to smart grids, which involve the allocation of resources to meet demands. This falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT), as well as algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG) which are often used in optimization problems. The paper also deals with control systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT) which are relevant to the management of smart grids.
